{
  "texts": [
    "The time is now right for qualitative and interpretive researchers to take advantage of AI-driven technologies like ChatGPT and other LLMs.",
    "Advances in the availability of digital text and processing power have resulted in large language models trained on a vast corpus of diverse text data from the internet, including books, articles, websites, and other publicly available sources, making these models particularly useful tools for dealing with text.",
    "Recent research systematically tests and documents that large language models and other technological developments are increasingly reliable and effective qualitative research tools (e.g., Do et al., 2022; Gilardi et al., 2023; Törnberg, 2023).",
    "Furthermore, the accessibility of ChatGPT and some other models to those without a background in data science makes using them feasible for researchers without specialized training.",
    "Although researchers should understand the basics of ChatGPT or whatever LLM they work with, using these tools requires no prior computer programming knowledge and there is no need for researchers to be competent in computer and data science."
  ]
}